==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Outpost
<hw>Out"post`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Mil.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>A post or station without the limits of a camp, or at
a distance from the main body of an army, for observation of the
enemy.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The troops placed at such a
station.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Outpour</ent>⟦br⟧
